cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about sound search and the development of two web-based search engines for sound. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper evaluates the user experience of the two search engines. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper discusses algorithms for sound search and compares two different approaches. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as the paper involves text descriptions and vocal imitation, which are related to natural language processing. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with audio content and search engines for multimedia data.
